It was announced this week that local film The Wound, will get its world premiere at the Sundance Film festival to be held next month.The film, starring Nakhane Tour , depicts a story of Kwanda, a gay teenager, who travels from the city to a rural area of his family's origin to be circumcised in a traditional rites-of-passage into manhood.The film is directed by John Trengove, who has worked on a number of TV hits, including Hopeville.A documentary by a French filmmaker about Winnie Madikizela Mandela will also be premiered at the festival. 